# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# ApexHunter DAST Agent - Environment Configuration
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── LLM Provider Selection ─────────────────────────
# Which provider to use for strategic planning (heavy reasoning)
# Options: azure, bedrock, ollama, openai, gemini
APEX_PLANNER_PROVIDER=azure

# Which provider to use for tactical execution (fast, cheap)
# Options: azure, bedrock, ollama, openai, gemini
APEX_EXECUTOR_PROVIDER=ollama

# ── Azure OpenAI ───────────────────────────────────
AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-azure-api-key-here
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com/
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o
AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-08-01-preview

# ── AWS Bedrock ────────────────────────────────────
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key
AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_BEDROCK_MODEL_ID=anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022-v2:0

# ── Local Ollama ───────────────────────────────────
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3

# ── Google Gemini (via Gemini CLI OAuth) ───────────
# Uses the OAuth token from the Gemini CLI (~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json).
# Run `gemini` once to authenticate via browser, then set provider to "gemini".
# This bypasses AI Studio API key rate limits by reusing the CLI's OAuth quota.
# The client ID and secret below are the Gemini CLI's public OAuth desktop-app
# credentials (hardcoded in the CLI source). They are NOT secret.
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro
GEMINI_OAUTH_CREDS_PATH=~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json
GEMINI_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-gemini-cli-oauth-client-id
GEMINI_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your-gemini-cli-oauth-client-secret

# ── Agent Behavior ─────────────────────────────────
# Max concurrent requests for race condition testing
APEX_MAX_CONCURRENT=20

# Circuit breaker: % of 5xx errors to trigger auto-sleep
APEX_CIRCUIT_BREAKER_THRESHOLD=5

# Seconds to sleep when circuit breaker trips
APEX_AUTOSLEEP_DURATION=900

# Speed factor when resuming after auto-sleep (0.0-1.0)
APEX_RESUME_SPEED_FACTOR=0.5

# Max crawling depth for the spider
APEX_MAX_DEPTH=10
